---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const guideData = {
  title: 'Mixo AI Website Builder: Complete Guide',
  description: 'Complete guide to Mixo AI website builder. Learn how to use Mixo for fast website generation, features, pricing, and tips for success.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const mixoFeatures = [
  {
    feature: 'AI Site Generation',
    description: 'Generate complete websites in under 60 seconds with AI assistance',
    benefit: 'Fastest time to live website of any builder'
  },
  {
    feature: 'Built-in SEO',
    description: 'Automatic SEO optimization with meta tags and structured data',
    benefit: 'Better search rankings without extra work'
  },
  {
    feature: 'Easy Editing',
    description: 'Intuitive visual editor for content and design customization',
    benefit: 'Anyone can use it, no technical skills needed'
  },
  {
    feature: 'Blogging Platform',
    description: 'Built-in blog functionality for content marketing',
    benefit: 'Content marketing and SEO capabilities included'
  },
  {
    feature: 'Analytics',
    description: 'Built-in analytics to track visitor behavior',
    benefit: 'Understand your audience without third-party tools'
  },
  {
    feature: 'Affordable Pricing',
    description: 'Starting at $9/month with generous free tier',
    benefit: 'Best value for budget-conscious users'
  }
];

const useCases = [
  {
    useCase: 'Landing Pages',
    description: 'Perfect for product launches, events, or marketing campaigns',
    why: 'Fast setup, built-in SEO, lead capture forms'
  },
  {
    useCase: 'Personal Portfolios',
    description: 'Showcase your work, skills, or projects',
    why: 'Clean templates, easy customization, professional results'
  },
  {
    useCase: 'Small Business Sites',
    description: 'Professional web presence for local businesses',
    why: 'Affordable, includes key features, easy to maintain'
  },
  {
    useCase: 'MVP Testing',
    description: 'Validate business ideas quickly before heavy investment',
    why: 'Fastest route to live site, minimal cost, easy iteration'
  },
  {
    useCase: 'Event Sites',
    description: 'Weddings, conferences, or special occasions',
    description: 'Simple setup, RSVP forms, beautiful photo galleries'
  }
];
---

<Layout title={guideData.title} description={guideData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does Mixo AI website builder work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo uses AI to generate complete websites in under 60 seconds. Simply describe your business or project, answer a few questions about your goals and preferences, and Mixo AI creates a complete website with pages, content, images, and styling. You can then customize everything using the intuitive visual editor. No technical skills required. Mixo handles hosting, SSL certificates, and provides built-in SEO optimization, making it the fastest way to get a professional website live."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Mixo really free?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo offers a generous free tier with no time limit. Free plans include AI generation, hosting, SSL certificate, and core features. Limitations include Mixo branding, no custom domain (unless you upgrade), and limited storage. Paid plans start at $9/month and remove branding, allow custom domains, and provide additional features. However, note that branding removal costs extra - the $9/month base plan still includes Mixo branding. Full pricing transparency: free tier with branding, $9/month for basic features with branding, additional fees for complete branding removal. The free tier is perfect for testing, personal projects, or budget websites."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What can I build with Mixo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo excels at: landing pages and marketing sites, personal portfolios and resumes, small business websites, event sites (weddings, conferences), MVP testing for startups, blogs and content sites, lead generation pages, and simple e-commerce (via integrations). Mixo is less suitable for: complex web applications, large e-commerce stores with many products, highly custom designs requiring pixel-perfect control, or sites requiring advanced functionality like user accounts and dashboards. For 90% of simple website needs, Mixo delivers excellent results quickly and affordably."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I migrate my Mixo site to another platform?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo does NOT offer code export or easy migration. Unlike Framer or Webflow where you can export code and host elsewhere, Mixo sites are locked to their platform. This is the biggest limitation: if you build on Mixo, you're committed to their platform or you'll need to rebuild from scratch if you leave. For long-term projects or businesses expecting growth, this lock-in matters. Consider Framer or Webflow if you want portability through code export. Mixo works best for: temporary sites, MVP testing, landing pages with limited lifespan, or projects where platform lock-in isn't a concern. If portability matters to you, choose a different builder from the start."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does Mixo compare to Durable for AI website generation?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo and Durable are both fast AI website builders, but they serve different needs. Mixo ($9/mo) excels at content sites and blogging with better writing features, article management, and SEO tools. Durable ($15/mo) focuses on business sites with built-in CRM, lead management, and business tools. Speed: both generate sites in under 60 seconds. Design quality: Mixo has slightly better templates. AI generation: both are fast and similar quality. Choose Mixo if you need: blogging, content marketing, or content-heavy sites. Choose Durable if you need: CRM features, lead tracking, or business-focused websites. For most simple sites, the difference comes down to pricing ($9 vs $15) and whether you need Mixo's content features or Durable's business tools."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Mixo have e-commerce capabilities?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo does NOT have native e-commerce features. You cannot sell products directly through Mixo like you can with Squarespace Commerce, Shopify, or Wix Stores. However, you can integrate third-party solutions: Gumroad for digital products, Stripe Payment Links for simple sales, or embed Buy Buttons from other platforms. This approach works for: selling 1-5 products, digital downloads, or simple payment collection. For serious e-commerce with: many products, inventory management, complex shipping, or tax calculation - choose a dedicated e-commerce platform instead. Mixo works best as a marketing/landing page that drives traffic to external checkout rather than a full e-commerce solution."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are Mixo's limitations compared to Framer or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo's key limitations: no code export (platform lock-in), limited design customization compared to Framer/Webflow, simpler templates that can look generic, no native e-commerce, less advanced features overall. Framer offers: better design quality (9.5/10 vs Mixo's 7.5/10), code export for portability, more modern templates, stronger portfolio features. Webflow offers: complete design control, powerful CMS, complex interactions, professional development capabilities. Mixo wins on: price ($9 vs $15-45), simplicity, speed to launch, blogging features. Choose Mixo for budget sites and quick launches. Choose Framer/Webflow for design quality and long-term flexibility."
